Source: Asia News, Fri 15 Jul 2005 [edited]
<http://asia.news.yahoo.com/050715/kyodo/d8bbkfm01.html>

Indonesia: Avian Influenza Now Suspected as Cause of 3 Recent Deaths
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Indonesian Health Minister Siti Fadillah Supari said on Fri 15 Jul
2005 that avian influenza is now suspected in the deaths of a man and
his 2 young daughters during the past 10 days. Sardikin Giriputro,
Chief of a Health Ministry medical team, told reporters on Thu 14 Jul
2005 that at least 2 of the 3 deaths were most likely caused by acute
cluster pneumonia, not avian influenza. The health minister said
further testing has shown that avian influenza may indeed be the
cause [of the deaths]. A man died Tuesday last week at a hospital in
Tangerang, Banten Province, while his 10-year-old daughter died on
Saturday, and his 8-year-old daughter on Thursday morning. [see
comment below regarding discrepancies in reported ages of the
deceased]
In June 2005, the Indonesian government announced its 1st bird flu
case, saying a farm worker in South Sulawesi Province had been
exposed to avian influenza but was not infected by the virus [i.e.
did not develop symptoms of infection - Mod.CP].
--
