Indonesia: Avian Influenza Suspected as Cause of 3 Recent Deaths
----------------------------------------------------------------
Indonesia suspects 3 recent deaths in a single family were caused by
avian influenza, Health Minister Siti Fadillah Supari said on Friday
[15 Jul 2005].
"We suspect it was caused by avian influenza. The 2nd test showed
there are signs this may be caused by avian influenza," Supari said.
--
